Main floor office/retail opportunity. The current space includes a large reception/meeting space, smaller office area, private washroom and kitchenette/breakroom. As Saskatchewan’s newest and fastest growing city, Warman is boasts a population of over 11,500 residents and a projected five year average growth rate of 11.02%. Located just 10km north of Saskatoon, this former bedroom community continues to be an attractive location for both commercial and residential development.

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text: Meadows Market has approximately 161,000 SF of retail in a high-visibility, power centre setting. It is anchored by Costco, and now features Marshalls, Petsmart, Dollar Tree, Co-op Liquor, Visions, Tim Hortons, McDonald’s and ScotiaBank as major tenants. CRU and Pad Site opportunities are available with convenient access to and from the #16 highway and the Rosewood neighborhood.

Located on 2nd Avenue N in City Park, this single-story retail/office space is well situated near the downtown core. The 1,820 SF suite is well suited for a salon, spa or medical tenant  as this space is well equipped with reception area, 9 sinks (plumbing for 12), 6 rooms (potential for 7), over $50,000 in spa/salon renovations. The landlord will provide the space in a warm shell condition for office or retail tenants.

Located along two main highway junctions, this site lies in the heart of what will filter traffic in from the Trans-Canada and highway 4. The area immediately surrounding SunTerrace Meadows includes two new schools, the new Cypress Regional Hospital, and the new Cypress House nursing home. The nearby commercial services and the development plans for the site are designed to further serve the daily retail needs of the community. New developments surrounding SunTerrace include big box retail, restaurants, and grocery stores. Opportunities exist for retailers looking to establish an early presence in a desired location in this growing community.
